Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Credicorp, Scotiabank Peru

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-23T18:24:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-credicorp-scotiabank-peru.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:09 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell for a fifth session, losing 1
percent to 18,828.90. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 2.2
percent to 2,372.54.  Industrial and banking stocks slumped on growing investor
concern that policy makers will be unable to avert another
global recession, said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-
based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1)  (CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of
 Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, fell 1.9 percent to
5.10 soles. Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll
Seafood ASA, dropped 3.6 percent to 27 centimos.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP) 
, Peru’s largest financial-services holding company,
slid 2.6 percent to $92.50.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE),
the local unit of  Canada ’s third-largest bank, declined 2
percent to 44 soles.  Gold and zinc miners dropped after the metals declined in
New York and  London .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, plunged 8.1 percent to $38.80.
Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and lead producer
controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., dropped
4.8 percent to 5 soles. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE),
the Lima-based zinc and silver mining company, declined 4
percent to 95 centimos.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a
Canadian gold exploration company, fell for a third session,
losing 3.9 percent to $2.69.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
